  "text": "As mentioned in Sec. I, we are interested in the following four trial states; (i) the Laughlin state, Ψ 333 , (ii) the fermionic Haffnian state, Ψ Hf , which is shown to be equivalent to AΨ 551 under the proper understanding of the ground-state degeneracy in the torus geometry, (iii) the antisymmetrized product state of two CF seas at 1/6 filling, AΨ6 CFS⊗ 6 CFS , and (iv) the PH conjugate of the Z 4 parafermion state, C PH Ψ Z4 , where Ψ Z4 is identified as AΨ 330 under the proper understanding of the groundstate degeneracy in the torus geometry. Below, we provide the concrete mathematical forms of the trial states and explain how to obtain them numerically by applying the antisymmetrization and the PH conjugation operators onto the relevant bilayer quantum Hall states. See Ref. [CITATION_1] for details on how to perform the antisymmetrization and the PH conjugation operators in second quantization.",
